====================================================================
PURPOSE
====================================================================

This document is the single source of truth for Project Atlas.

Every coding task, implementation prompt, architecture decision,
feature request, roadmap discussion, and release decision must align
with this document.

No implementation may knowingly violate this Release Master Plan.

This document exists to:

• Maintain architectural consistency

• Preserve long-term project memory

• Prevent duplicate implementation

• Record completed milestones

• Define implementation priorities

• Document engineering decisions

• Track release readiness

• Guide every future development session

This document is updated after every completed implementation session.

====================================================================
PRODUCT VISION
====================================================================

Atlas is an Autonomous AI Operating System for Inventors.

Atlas is NOT:

• a chatbot

• a note-taking application

• a project manager

• a document generator

• a collection of AI prompts

Atlas functions as an autonomous company.

Each department performs meaningful work, collaborates with other
departments, produces structured outputs, records evidence, updates the
CEO, and automatically continues work whenever dependencies are
satisfied.

The founder should spend time making strategic decisions—not managing
tasks.

====================================================================
PRODUCT PRINCIPLES
====================================================================

These principles are permanent.

1.

Atlas performs work instead of giving advice.

------------------------------------------------------------

2.

Every department produces measurable outputs.

------------------------------------------------------------

3.

Every department consumes structured outputs from previous departments.

------------------------------------------------------------

4.

Atlas automatically continues work whenever dependencies are satisfied.

------------------------------------------------------------

5.

The founder should only be involved for:

• Legal approvals

• Strategic decisions

• Physical-world actions

• External relationships

------------------------------------------------------------

6.

Engineering remains the technical source of truth.

------------------------------------------------------------

7.

Native CAD remains the geometry source of truth.

------------------------------------------------------------

8.

Manufacturing remains the production source of truth.

------------------------------------------------------------

9.

Patent Intelligence remains the intellectual-property source of truth.

------------------------------------------------------------

10.

Every implementation must move Atlas closer to becoming a fully
autonomous inventor operating system.

