====================================================================

Priority 1

Complete the Autonomous Operating System.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 2

Complete all persistent intelligence layers.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 3

Complete department-to-department autonomy.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 4

Complete Founder Experience simplification.

------------------------------------------------------------

Priority 5

Polish Version 1.0.

====================================================================
RELEASE MILESTONES
====================================================================

The following milestones define the official implementation order.

A milestone is complete only when:

• Code is merged

• Tests pass

• Production deployment succeeds

• Regression verification succeeds

• Existing architecture remains intact

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-001 — Autonomous Orchestrator Foundation

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Created the core orchestration engine responsible for coordinating every
Atlas department.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-002 — Architecture Audit & Execution Consistency

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Unified execution architecture and removed conflicting execution paths.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-003 — Unified Department Execution

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Ensured every department executes through one orchestration pipeline.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-004 — Founder Experience Messaging

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Improved founder-facing communication while preserving architecture.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-005 — Workspace Deduplication

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Established canonical workspaces and eliminated duplicated information
throughout Atlas.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-006 — Autonomous Execution Engine

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Implemented the event-driven execution engine with dependency-aware
queues, retries, approval gates, lifecycle tracking, and execution
history.

Release Impact

Atlas became capable of autonomously coordinating work across multiple
departments.

====================================================================
====================================================================

AT-007 — Native Engineering Intelligence Engine

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Established one persistent Engineering Intelligence Model per invention.

Major Deliverables

• Persistent Engineering Model

• Parametric Product Model

• Component hierarchy

• Assembly relationships

• Functional requirements

• Manufacturing requirements

• Materials

• Dimensions

• Tolerances

• Engineering validation

• Design-rule validation

• Engineering Package generation

• CEO Engineering Summary

• Immutable engineering revisions

• Downstream synchronization

Release Impact

Engineering became the authoritative technical source of truth for Atlas.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-008 — Native CAD Foundation

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Created Atlas' native geometry architecture that future CAD generation,
simulation, and visualization will build upon.

Major Deliverables

• Native CAD Model

• Parametric sketches

• Geometry entities

• Constraint system

• Feature tree foundation

• Bodies

• Parts

• Assemblies

• Coordinate systems

• Reference planes

• Origin management

• CAD serialization

• Immutable CAD revisions

• CAD snapshots

• CAD diff engine

• Geometry validation

• Canonical CAD Package

Release Impact

Atlas now maintains its own internal geometric representation rather than
depending solely on engineering specifications.

------------------------------------------------------------

AT-009 — Manufacturing Intelligence

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Created a persistent Manufacturing Intelligence Model that evaluates how
an invention can realistically be produced.

Major Deliverables

• Manufacturing Readiness

• Manufacturing Constraints

• Manufacturing Risks

• Process Selection

• Material Compatibility

• Material Recommendations

• DFM Rule Engine

• Assembly Analysis

• Production Complexity

• Manufacturing Validation

• Manufacturing Package

• Manufacturing Revisions

Release Impact

Atlas now reasons about manufacturability using Engineering and CAD
without duplicating either model.

====================================================================
====================================================================

AT-010 — Patent Intelligence 2.0

STATUS

✅ COMPLETE

Purpose

Created a persistent Patent Intelligence Model that evaluates the
intellectual-property position of an invention by consuming Engineering,
CAD, and Manufacturing intelligence without duplicating their data.

Major Deliverables

• Patent Intelligence Model

• Prior-Art Knowledge Store

• Patent Landscape Analysis

• Novelty Assessment

• Patent Readiness Score

• Inventive Feature Catalog

• Claim Element Mapping

• Independent Innovation Mapping

• Prior-Art Conflict Tracking

• Design-Around Opportunity Framework

• Patent Risk Scoring

• Evidence Linking

• Technical Citation Tracking

• Immutable Patent Revisions

• Canonical Patent Package

Release Impact

Atlas now performs structured patent reasoning and maintains persistent
patent intelligence that future Licensing and Investor departments can
consume.

------------------------------------------------------------

