====================================================================
DAILY DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW
====================================================================

Every implementation session follows this sequence.

STEP 1

Read this document completely.

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 2

Identify the first unfinished milestone.

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 3

Review the previous completed milestone and its architecture.

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 4

Preserve all existing architecture.

Never rewrite completed systems unless correcting a critical defect.

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 5

Implement only the current milestone.

Do not skip ahead.

Do not begin future milestones.

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 6

Run verification.

Minimum required verification:

• Convex code generation

• TypeScript validation

• Focused milestone tests

• Full regression suite

• Production build

• Deployment verification

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 7

Report:

• Executive Summary

• Files Modified

• Architecture Decisions

• Features Implemented

• Database Changes

• API Changes

• Validation Rules

• Tests Executed

• Build Status

• Deployment Status

• Remaining Work

• Recommended Next Task

------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 8

Update ONLY this file:

docs/RELEASE_MANAGEMENT/ATLAS_RELEASE_MASTER_PLAN_v1.0.md

Do not create a new Release Master Plan.

====================================================================
TASK IMPLEMENTATION RULES
====================================================================

Every implementation task must follow these rules.

1.

Preserve existing architecture.

------------------------------------------------------------

2.

Maintain backward compatibility.

------------------------------------------------------------

3.

Consume existing intelligence layers instead of duplicating data.

------------------------------------------------------------

4.

Use the AT-006 Autonomous Execution Engine.

No polling.

No bypasses.

No duplicate execution paths.

------------------------------------------------------------

5.

All new intelligence must produce a canonical package consumable by
downstream departments.

------------------------------------------------------------

6.

All significant autonomous actions must be visible through the
CEO Command Center.

------------------------------------------------------------

7.

Every milestone must include deterministic validation.

------------------------------------------------------------

8.

Every completed milestone must pass the full regression suite before
deployment.

