====================================================================
FINAL OBJECTIVE
====================================================================

Project Atlas Version 1.0 is complete when a founder can submit an
invention once and Atlas autonomously coordinates every participating
department from concept through commercialization.

Atlas must:

• Maintain persistent knowledge across all departments.

• Perform meaningful work instead of providing advice.

• Generate structured deliverables for downstream departments.

• Coordinate autonomous execution through a single orchestration engine.

• Explain every significant decision through the CEO Command Center.

• Require founder input only for legal, financial, strategic, or
physical-world actions.

Success is measured not by the number of reports Atlas generates, but by
its ability to independently execute, coordinate, reason, and guide an
invention through the entire innovation lifecycle using a unified,
explainable, trustworthy, and extensible operating system.

